# Cursor Rules for Blog Project

## Tailwind CSS 4 Best Practices

- Always use Tailwind CSS 4 best practices and features
- Follow the new @theme inline syntax for custom configurations
- Use the new @import "tailwindcss" syntax instead of @tailwind directives

## Colors and Spacing

- **Always use theme colors and spacing values**
- **Never use inline/arbitrary colors or spacing** (e.g., avoid `text-[#152035]`, `p-[24px]`)
- If a color or spacing value doesn't exist in the theme:
  1. First, update `app/globals.css` to add it to the theme
  2. Then use the theme variable in your components
- Use CSS custom properties defined in `:root` for colors
- Reference theme values using Tailwind's utility classes (e.g., `text-heading`, `bg-background`)

## Color Scheme

Current theme colors:
- Background: `--background` (#fff6ef light, #02111a dark)
- Foreground: `--foreground` (#505050 light, #d6d6d6 dark)
- Heading: `--heading` (#152035 light, #ffffff dark)
- Accent (links/active): #f08e80

## Typography

- Headings: Use Crete Round font (`--font-crete-round`)
- Body: Use Work Sans font (`--font-work-sans`)
- Default font size: 16px

## Component Guidelines

- Prefer Server Components by default
- Use "use client" only when necessary (state, effects, browser APIs)
- Follow Next.js 16 App Router conventions
- Keep components focused and reusable

## File Organization

- Pages go in `app/` directory
- Reusable components in `components/` directory
- Utilities and helpers in `lib/` directory
- Blog posts in `posts/` directory (MDX format)

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first approach
- Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- Ensure all components work on mobile, tablet, and desktop

## Package Manager

- Always use `bun` as the package manager
- Use `bun install`, `bun add`, `bun remove` for package management
- Use `bun run` for running scripts

